This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories as it deals with deep neural networks and their quantization. It also involves optimization techniques, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of sinusoidal functions and regularization techniques may also place it under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the experimentation and analysis of results may also make it relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
